76561198011650742,Not Recommended,249630,21396135,"Posted: 22 February, 2016",all,HunterFX21,"I requested refund right away.It's fun for the first little while, but it doesn't take long to figure out that this game lacks any real content.I decided to research this game (wiki) after playing for a while.Here's my conclusion.There's a lack of monster and level diversity, there isn't a huge variety of items, there's no way to sell items (not a huge issue, but still worth mentioning).The game engine was well made, the dungeons are somewhat fun to explore, but it's easy to see how this game would get repetitive fast. It's strikingly similar to Minecraft, yet different. While Minecraft focuses on exploration and diversity (biomes, items, creatures, etc.), the developers of this game only chose to focus on dungeon exploration with little creativity in respect to monsters, items, and biome.I understand content takes time to add, but this game is already in beta, lacks a solid update history, and most importantly - diversity in monster, characters, and items. Let's get real, this game has been out since 2013 and it is now 2016 - So where's the content?While this game may provide fun for a short while, I would stay away from this one until the developers can get their act together.Consumers work hard for their money and deserve a polished game - this one is just not there yet."
