,Not Recommended,249630,21922371,"Posted: 19 March, 2016",all,SheridanR,"I beat this game on my very first try in under two hours, and I've just realized that that means I can get a refund for it, which I'm now sure to do. For what this game is, it looks and feels very, very nice. The pixel art, engine, and polish on this game are all very well done, and the beginning of the game left a pretty good taste in my mouth (which may be more than some people say for my game, Barony). However, this game simply has no depth to it. The music is very limited and loops constantly, so even though it sounds nice at first it gets tiring quickly. There are no skill trees, there is no diversity in each playthrough, and the mechanical variety of the game is just so low -- it's hard to describe, but gameplay-wise, there's no MEAT to this game.I was not aware that this game even existed when I made my own first-person ""roguelike"", and I've only just now played it, so I fully admit I may be biased -- but after having beaten this game, as well as coming away from it from an initially positive impression, I have to say I am not too impressed with this game now. The developers are very smart and talented, but I just don't think they put in enough effort with this game. This is probably what I'd call a wasted opportunity for some really nice first-person RPG goodness."
76561198043362849,Recommended,249630,7785853,"Posted: 27 November, 2013",all,comma fucker upper,"Delver is an addicting, first-person, dungeon crawler with procedurally generated dungeons. It is still of course unfinished, so there are bugs to fixed and new things to be added, but it is still very satisfying. However, it doesn't really bring much new to the table. It's still a beautiful game in both sound, graphics, and gameplay, but it's not quite a masterpiece. It's like one of Picasso's early paintings. It's still great, but not like his later paintings which truly defined him. Nonetheless, it is still tons of fun to play, and keeps on bringing you back again and again, even after you've beaten the game. Despite not being completely inventive, it still is a lovely game, and even for $7.99, considering that it is still is in early access, i highly reccomend it."
