76561198004368051,Recommended,249630,28335343,"Posted: 12 December, 2016",all,DFuxa,"Delver is a first person action rogue-like where you are delving into a dungeon to fetch the orb and ascend.... Essentially this is Rogue if Rogue was a first person action game. You use various weapons, wands, potions, and food as to transverse down different styles of levels fighting various enemies - some that fly!Some of the best things about this game though is that it does well to allow for pattern recognition from enemies - allowing for skill players to dispatch enemies with deft movement and attacks. Its traps can be somewhat simple, but they can sometimes lead to some interesting situations - and a clever player can always 'trigger' them before stepping on them.In many ways, this is a very simple game as far as first person action rogue-likes go, and it has been somewhat slow to develop - being in Early Access long after Barony for instance was done. It doesn't have multiplayer and it can feel somewhat easy to play and should be easily beaten within the first few tries by more competent players. There is perhaps a bit of a lack in what you can do and experience for the price tag of the game.Overall I do recommend this game, though I wish there was more depth to it. As it is now it lacks somewhat in replayability - which for many players is going to be a glowing problem. But it does have the potential to be a fun little game to play if develop continues on it."
