76561198072680595,Recommended,249630,23077631,"Posted: 19 May, 2016",all,benvlieg,"Delver is a great first person rogue like. You have to descend into a mine to uncover to artifact at the bottom. Being a rogue like the game has randomly generated levels and perma-death. The levels are generally good. I have only encountered one area I couldn't reach.  The combat is fun. There are magic wands, melee weapons and bows and arrows. Wands have a limited use but are very powerful. Melee weapons are fun to use. Dagger do less damage that axes bur are faster. There are a variety of melee weapons. Bows are fun to use, with a great ranged attack but they have a limited arrow supply and are useless in close range combat. The game is great in its current state and receives updates every six months. The game got mod support recently which adds a lot of value."
