,Recommended,249630,8592873,"Posted: 6 January, 2014",all,onepeach,"Having played this game a long time ago, I was unimpressed. Since then there has been a significant graphical update (and a sale) which pushed me to buy it, and I do not regret it. Keep in mind, though that this is an early game, so there are still some unimplemented 'core' features.+ A real-time roguelike with engaging first-person combat. Very enjoyable combat.+ I do like that the levels have their own styles, rather than being the same shape with different art.+ The stats have a very definite impact on your gameplay.- I don't think there's enough variety in the random level generation to make it worth playing through more than once. Especially the damned sewer levels.- I don't think Delver (right now) has much replay value. I found just maxxing your Health to the exclusion of all other stats is really the most effective strategy. I did that, beat the boss, and practically waltzed back up to the surface, orb in hand, without a scratch. What did I have to show for it? Nothing except money. Exactly the same thing I would have had if I died to the end boss.- I never bought anything from the shop anyway. There's plenty of free loot in the dungeon, better than what you can buy. I found no reason to collect nor spend money. Maybe shops in the dungeon would help because I often need a specific item, like a potion or wand. I'm a big fan of the wands*. Please put in more kinds of wand.*Totally not guns.~ What if beating the Lich unlocked lower levels?~ What if lower levels unlocked more items from the shop/more shops?It's a fun game, which I enjoyed more than I expected to, but it is not done yet! Very playable, but feels empty and pointless once you've beat the Lich once. I was kinda hoping for a whole new dungeon to open up, but it's early days."
