,Recommended,249630,8499344,"Posted: 1 January, 2014",all,Sucy,"A pretty casual roguelike experience. As of this post, I played it a few times and quickly made it far; only dying to either burst (Didn't get enough health or armor), or my own stupidity. It's very short, which I suppose is a good thing for a game like this. It's easy, but you still can't face-check anything until you get lucky enough with weapons, armor, and stock piles of food / potions. It does get easier as the game goes on, which is a bad and good thing.The stronger you get, the less trouble you have and are capable of dealing with most creatures. But at the same time, before you get to that stage you struggle and have to back-peddle swing many monsters to survive. You do get a lot of wands I have noticed, which trivializes a lot of encounters; which should be their purpose. But the purpose is way too strong when you get a wand drop every other kill. And the mages almost always drop them, even if they are absolute crap -- it's a ranged weapon and you take 0 damage from back-peddling and killing the enemy.Stats are not very clear on what they do besides Attack, Speed, and Health. It's obvious you deal more damage with Attack, move faster when you up speed, and gain more health everytime you level it up. Agility was very vague on what it did, and I still don't feel the effects. The same goes for defense and magic. They feel either too weak to actually present themselves as useful, or are just not straight forward enough.I would recommend this game on sale. It's a decent time waster for a few hours, but it has very little to give after you play through it just a few times."
,Recommended,249630,10800972,"Posted: 25 June, 2014",all,Blood_Wraith,"A fairly short FPS roguelike with a Minecraft feel to the graphics and the terrain, as well as the inventory, minus weapon/armor durability, your equipment is indestructible. Except for magic wands/scrolls, which have limited charges but can be very useful.There are also several different colored potions which effects are randomized each playthrough, most of them are helpful, while one of them is poison, so be careful.Then you got your EXP system and leveling up system where you can choose between several stats, I just usually get health every level when I can, you're gonna need it.The general goal is to go down several floors of dungeons, always having the same tileset/theme but a different layout each playthrough, and get the treasure, and then traverse all the way back to camp from where you started as angry monsters chase you after stealing their treasure.A decent enough roguelike, it was fun and lasted about 2 hours so far, going through the game twice. Could use more variety and maybe achievements in the future."
