,Recommended,249630,14699458,"Posted: 28 February, 2015",all,An Earl By Any Other Name,"This game is impressive, so far.Do you like challenge? Delver has it. It's deceptively simple; three equipment selections with apparently-linear upgrading; you only choose whether to equip heavier armor at a loss of speed. Amulets and rings? Straightforward. Weapons? Same deal, though they can be enchanted for bonus elemental damage. All in all it seems like the sort of game you can fully-understand in 30 minutes or less.And then, on your second or third play(or fourth or fifth), you get far enough. And you realize there's a *purpose* behind what you're doing. Me, I thought you just got to wander, fight things, find gear, and satisfy that itch to hoard, but there's more! And if you thought it was hard going deeper and deeper.... just wait for the trek back up. But that's all I'll say, as I don't want to spoil anything.Delver is already well-worth the $7.99 it's currently selling for. The visuals are simple and remind me of Minecraft(despite not actually adhering to the same visual format at all), the sprite style is deceptively innocent, colors are vibrant and the lighting is very complimentary to the atmosphere. If you're like me, you'll find yourself creeping, ears sharp. What was that noise? Where did it come from, exactly? What made it??Like I said, it's worth the small price tag, and that's when you know an Early Access game deserves to be Early Access. This isn't a case of ""well, it's probably gonna turn into something great given time!"" at all. Delver is great, and if you want to pick it up now and get your money's worth early-on, then you'll already have it as it continues to grow bigger and better. Personally, I think I made the right choice hands-down."
,Recommended,249630,31195197,Posted: 17 April,all,Baka.,"Delver is extremely charming.  It's a nice, simple dungeon crawler that you can have a cup of tea and play, or pick up and play whenever you want.  There is a mobile version as well, and I'm sure it works very well as that too.  It is /very/ simple, but it is because of that that it is very reminiscent of earlier dungeon crawling titles.  I think this is a fantastic game for beginners of the genre and even after you've spent some time with it, it never really loses its luster.  You may grow disinterested after you've played for a few hours, but with mod support and stuff you can really revive the dead horse if you want -  That said it's always really cheap and it is genuine fun for a few hours.  Try it out atleast. :)"
