,Not Recommended,249630,15888572,"Posted: 18 May, 2015",all,"mess with Chen, get the horns","Overall the game is okay, a very basic ""rogue-like-lite"". It suffers from being a bit weak in scope, but the gameplay is tight. The ending is unbearably annoying, and only has one real playstyle you can do to beat it. I can only suggest the game for $2 or less.If you've ever played a ""real"" rogue-like, like Nethack (or other ASCIIs) you'll be very disappointed. The game is incredibly limited, the ""RPG"" element is ultrabasic, with only 2-3 stats actually being useful. There is no character magic, and the game scales pretty linearly. I actually got more out of building up in the first or second dungeons, because while deeper levels bring harder enemies, the rewards are worse.The author put in official mod support, though there is no Steam Workshop. I did not try any of that.Note on other's reviews: Only the first and second dungeons are ""procedurally generated"" in the normal sense. The others are randomized, but not completely random. It makes the game more interesting, but there are next to no items and as mentioned."
