,Recommended,249630,33548473,Posted: 14 July,all,RaggitySkags,"For about a year, I've been searching game stores in my Toronto neighbourhood, looking for a little gem on the PS2 called Eternal Ring by FromSoftware; perhaps you've heard of it? I never was able to find it and when it came on Playstation Store, I decided not to buy it in favour of Friday the 13th, the resulting situation ending in me hocking my PS4 due to a lack of customer support and quality control.Then I came to Steam and thought I may never know the fun of Eternal Ring again, Delver has proved me wrong. It's like a more accessable, minecrafty version. Endearing to me right from the start, I started to play not knowing much, learning that the potions work off of a RNG, just like DeathState, you can build your Delver from the first time you set foot in a dungeon until you happen to fall victim to some devious creatures or traps, at which point you must start from scratch - save for your gold... your sweet, sweet gold. This allows later playthroughs some leniency and sets you up so you can at least have an idea of how you are going to build your Delver for the current new playthough.In summation, buy this game! It's totally worth it for the price, if you don't like it you can just refund it, but I guarentee you'll find yourself dropping hours upon hours on it if you find it's your style. I've only played for about an hour and half at the time of writing but I can say I'll be putting many more hours in before I'm through. Happy delving, fellow Delvers!"
