,Not Recommended,249630,14106009,"Posted: 21 January, 2015",all,Mercykiller,this game has serious content issues
,Not Recommended,249630,34025088,Posted: 4 August,all,DoctorXOR,"I've put a lot of hours into this game (many more than Steam shows), and unfortunately the complete lack of statistical balance destroys what would be a really captivating and enjoyable version of Minecraft. The dungeon generation, music, and art are fantastic and initially kept me coming back for more, but the better I become at the game, the more infuriating it is to play and the less I can motivate myself to adventure further.Money is useless. Not only is the drop rate absurdly low, but there are only two places to purchase items - at the beginning of the run, and just after the first two floors. It's ridiculous that I have to play 3+ runs to the boss just to get enough gold for one good item at the shop. And then the stores are so early that it's pretty much a waste to spend your money because you're bound to spend it all on that run where you accidentally get pushed into lava by a monster you didn't see. At the shop, you never feel like you're making a good run better.Weapons are impossibly underpowered. At least 50% of the melee weapons you find on a given run you won't even want as backup due to random stat penalties. ""Let's see, unholy dagger... +4 attack and -6 defense??"" It's very rare that I even put on armor I find because the speed penalties are similarly high to the point where it takes you 10 minutes just to walk across one floor without fighting (and as anyone who has played past the boss knows, speed is REALLY important at the end of the game). Then you have magic wands, which come in two varieties: 1) fireball, which are absolutely wonderful but only have 6-12 shots (and usually insta-kill you if you hit something that is in melee range), and 2) all the other wands that are bad because they do so little damage, no matter how much you level up magic.If that weren't enough, weapons break after a certain number of hits. Your inventory is way too small (24 slots) for the game to force you to carry around 6+ weapons because all the good (damage) weapons you found were in bad condition.Finally, endgame. Actually getting to the boss is a healthy and enjoyable challenge. But then enemies pretty much flood out of the walls. Before the last few updates I was able to get ALMOST all the way back to the top of the dungeon. As of the last update, I can't get out of the boss room. I just had an amazingly lucky run with all the right items - I beat the boss, spent about 10 minutes in that room hacking away with my best weapon, gained 3 levels (each level gains you all your HP back), broke that weapon and 2 more, and then died because the enemies were simply spawning too fast for me to walk out the narrow hallway. My stats were 56 HP, 30 AC, something like 30 ATK with a fast-attacking Dusk and at least +2 default speed (with full armor). Every time I would get halfway down the path, enemies would continue to spawn and attack me from behind, forcing me to retreat and clear my back.It's an addicting experience with a great foundation, but ultimately until the endgame (among other issues) gets fixed, I can't recommend a game that makes you feel like you've wasted your time with impossible goals. If I had gotten out of the dungeon, I don't even think I would have felt the victory. Only thing that can get you out right now is lucky enemy spawns and running, which any monkey with a Shift key could pull off eventually."
