,Recommended,249630,8570581,"Posted: 5 January, 2014",all,Kektimus,"Great gem showing great promise!It does currently suffer some from a somewhat wonky and inconsistent interface (things in the action bar are both selected and used when their corresponding number is pressed depending on the type of item) and it uses I and M binding for inventory and map, respectively, which doesn't really fit a quite fast-paced type of game. Yet, it's a roguelike that is very easy to learn. It perhaps sacrifices some management depth to instead put more bang into the actual action parts, with interesting charge attacks that require you to time your movement to land your blows. Then there are some bugs, some rare instant unexplainable deaths, alt-tab fullscreen issues. After a certain point, enemies start appearing everywhere and even in front of you, in a way that feels... a bit cheap. But - it's not finished.It's rather short, and I like that. Hopefully with time, the shortness of it will be compensated with variety each playthrough. I've only played it 3 times, beaten it once (failed to beat it on my second playthrough due to instant unexplainable death), and all the times felt... very similar, but not identical. Not much reason for me to play it again at this point once I've beaten it right now.Delicious graphics. I've always loved low res pixel art because it gets my brain working to fill in the gaps and to create detail where there is none and makes at least me actually immerse myself far more than in ""HD"" games.Anyway - it's fun as it is, and I'm looking forward to future updates."
