,Recommended,249630,10969342,"Posted: 30 June, 2014",all,Nth RooCH,"Fantastic old school dungeon crawler. Given its price, this is a really smart, visually charming, pick-up-'n'-play crawler that manages to have entertaining combat, somewhat varied enemies and plenty of loot to work through. The dungeon levels are randomised, and each play has 7 levels, the last of which contains the Orb you're after. Grinding through each level to the end is great, and battling back up with the orb is even more challenging. There's a very small upgrade element, but by vast majority this is just one of those wee games you have that you jump into occasionally for a quick run around. No strings, no commitment, just a quick half hour of fun whenever you need it. Highly recommended."
