76561198089080273,Recommended,249630,19132786,"Posted: 17 November, 2015",all,RetrO,"DescriptionDelver is a first-person dungeon-crawling RPG. Its graphics are very sharp and appealing. When you die, you have to start the game over again. Combat is interesting, but, at some times, extremely repetitive. The potions give random effects determined at the starting generation of a new game. Enemies are cool and have slightly varied ways of combat. You can level up and use points to upgrade certain skills, and weapons vary a fair amount.Should I buy it?Yes. It's a great game, and new content is confirmed to come, but the game get's boring after five or so hours of total gameplay. You can easily mod the game with new weapons, armor, dungeon rooms, enemies, meshes, items - pretty much everything! The community is very small, and I hope it grows more soon.RatingI'll give Delver an 8/10.It's great for short, 45 minute bursts of gameplay, but any longer can often get boring. A few mods are being developed, one of which is a desert crypt dungeon mod which has an early version you can play. I really hope the developer, pardon me forgetting his name, adds more content soon, seeing as the game, once you beat it, gets boring after a while."
