76561198008598012,Recommended,249630,13655608,"Posted: 27 December, 2014",all,distractionbeast,"This is easily one of the most immediately enjoyable games I've played.  It takes the familiar rogue-like formula and gives it an unusual first-person treatment and a surprising amount of depth from its seemingly simple system.  If you are a fan of hack-and-slash, stat-based RPGs, rouge-likes, or just a quick, accessible action game, Delver delivers.My only gripes are with the difficult inventory menu.  It would be nice if the game paused while it was active and it's hard to get in and out of quickly.  I haven't found a way of identifying potions besides trial and error, and with limited health restoration, this can be deadly.  Random death is not good.Also, there are places where jumping feels needed, but there seems to be no jump feature.  It never breaks the game, but I notice the lack of it."
