,Recommended,249630,13901812,"Posted: 8 January, 2015",all,Jotakusan,"I love this game, it's more than worth the cheap price and it is a great time waster. I've spent quite a bit more time on this game than Steam says, on both my Mac and PC and it runs perfectly on both. Which is saying a lot when most games can not run more than 20fps on low graphics settings on my Macbook Pro. You can hardly tell that this game is still in alpha as I have not come across any bugs or issues. The only issue I have with this game is the fact that when I die I lose all of my stuff and any of my upgrades and have to start from the beginning. I understand that this is a feature of the game, but I would really love it if the developers made a game mode for players like me who do not really enjoy perma-death games and would rather have a fun dungeon crawler where I can save my progress. I would still recommend this game to anyone looking for a fun little first person dungeon crawler."
