,Recommended,249630,31129616,Posted: 13 April,all,TopNaut,"I've had this game in my inventory for a while now, and only recently decided to give it more than a few minutes of my time, and I'm kind of sad I didn't start playing it sooner. Delver might seem like something you'd glance over in the store and think ""oh boy another rogue-like"", but there's a certain charm to the game that kept me playing for a good 3ish hours before sitting down and writing this review. The game was very enjoyable for that span of time, but started to fall off as soon as I'd start a new run and have similar experiences from previous runs like running into the same items/enemies/equipment. (Thank goodness for mod support)I feel like this game shows good potential, and while I understand it's still in early access I think the biggest thing hindering it is the lack of content. As soon as there's more added to the game to make every run different even after hours of gameplay I could definitely see this game seeing great success.tl;dr Game is great and deserves some love, but lack of variety in items amongst other things makes replay value somewhat low"
,Recommended,249630,6426290,"Posted: 15 September, 2013",all,Gwenyvier,"Delver is a fun little first person rogue-like where you play as a nameless hero that goes through a (currently) small dungeon to find some important item. It is in early access currently so quite a bit is going to be added to it and its obviously still rather rough around the edges. It is 7 floors long only at the moment (again, EARLY ACCESS), the starting room of the first floor and the entire 7th floor are static. This may change in the future. Another thing worth mentioning is that the potions are bugged currently. No matter the color they always have random effects. This is almost guaranteed to be fixed in a future update as finding out what potions do is such an inherent part of the genre it would be a huge mark against the game otherwise.The game-play itself is quite fun, a decent amount of monster variety at the stage it's at, traps you can mess with to find out what they do, and very nice atmosphere. Good randomization of weapons, although the current options are rather limiting.As I stated a couple times already it is early access. In the future there will be more mobs, items, a potion fix (hopefully), and other things. The game will also be open so it can be modded and have texture packs added... there might even be some already, I did not check. And, for those that like playing dungeon master, a level editor so you can build your own fiendish dungeons to kill your friends in."
